&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181213/rss" title="una.im" style=" color: #D94306; font-size: 1.15em; line-height: 1.25em; font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;border-shape&lt;/code&gt;: The Future of the Non-Rectangular Web&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Una shares several fun experiments with the &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181214/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;border-shape&lt;/code&gt; property&lt;/a&gt;, calling it a ‚Äúgame-changer‚Äù for geometry on the web platform. It‚Äôs an early-stage feature so support is still behind a Chromium flag right¬†now.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Una Kravets &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;&lt;p&gt;üí° In other shape-related news, Noam Rosenthal shares some insights on &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181215/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;implementing &lt;code&gt;corner-shape&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a feature &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181216/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;you can use&lt;/a&gt; in mainstream Chrome and Edge right¬†now.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181158/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/c_limit,w_480,h_480,q_auto/copm/6a743f2e.png" width="145" height="145" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-left: 12px;     line-height: 100%;    "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181158/rss" title="youtu.be" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;What If Adding Auth to Your App Took One Command?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî &lt;code&gt;npx workos&lt;/code&gt; launches an AI agent that reads your project, detects your framework, and writes a complete auth integration into your existing codebase. It typechecks, builds, and self-corrects any errors. &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181158/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Just run &lt;code&gt;npx¬†workos&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;WorkOS &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #997 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181162/rss" title="piccalil.li" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;An In-Depth Guide to Customizing Lists with CSS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Richard goes into plenty of detail here, with code examples aplenty. You‚Äôll probably come away having learned something¬†here.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Richard Rutter &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181160/rss" title="scottjehl.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Standard HTML Video &amp;amp; Audio Lazy-Loading is Coming&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A progress update from Scott who has been working on standardizing lazy-loading the HTML video and audio element. He explains that ‚Äú&lt;em&gt;the feature is not yet standard, but the HTML spec proposal, platform tests, and browser patches have been in review for many weeks and support just landed behind a flag in Chrome¬†Canary&lt;/em&gt;‚Äù.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Scott Jehl &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
