&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.2em;"&gt;‚ö°Ô∏è&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase;    font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.2em;"&gt;IN BRIEF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚öôÔ∏è &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181164/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;The first beta of WordPress 7.0&lt;/a&gt; is now available. The big focus is the addition of real-time collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚¨ÜÔ∏è &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181217/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;The Navigation API is now Baseline Newly Available&lt;/a&gt; across all major browsers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üòÆ Someone has created an &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181165/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;x86 emulator in CSS&lt;/a&gt;, no JS! You'll need to open it in a Chromium-based browser.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üî∂ Zach has had a go at &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181166/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;creating a logo for HTML&lt;/a&gt;. The old orange shield for HTML 5 was likely the closest we've gotten to an 'official' logo for the language.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=" font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=" font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.2em;"&gt;üìô&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase;    font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.4em;"&gt;Articles, Opinions &amp;amp;¬†Tutorials&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em; "&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181167/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/cpress/image/upload/w_1280,e_sharpen:60,q_auto/v1771934137/ttup8uimlowuzrlbr5ow.png" width="640" style="    line-height: 100%;         "&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181167/rss" title="www.joshwcomeau.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Sprites on the Web&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Josh shows us the basics of frame-based animation, doing away with GIFs in favor of a fast CSS approach. He shares how to use things like the &lt;code&gt;object-fit&lt;/code&gt; property and the &lt;code&gt;steps()&lt;/code&gt; timing function to create neat, small-scale animated sprites. As always, lots of good examples and¬†demos.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Josh W. Comeau &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181161/rss" title="dbushell.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Everything You Never Wanted to Know About &lt;code&gt;visually-hidden&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Visually hiding content always throws up some accessibility questions ‚Äî this deep dive helps break it¬†down.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;David Bushell &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181170/rss" title="expo.dev" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Using Claude Skills to Build Mobile Apps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181171/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Expo's Claude Skills&lt;/a&gt; automatically apply Expo's best practices for building and shipping cross platform mobile¬†apps.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Expo &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;   color: #997 !important; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px;            "&gt;sponsor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;‚ñ∂¬†¬†&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181176/rss" title="www.youtube.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Smart Layouts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A roughly hour long talk in which Ahmad talks us through the process of using modern CSS to build layouts that are aware of their surroundings and¬†context.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Ahmad Shadeed &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181172/rss" title="css-tricks.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Potentially Coming to a Browser¬†&lt;code&gt;:near()&lt;/code&gt;¬†You&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Danny shares some ideas for how we could use the proposed &lt;code&gt;:near()&lt;/code&gt; pseudo-class ‚Äî a powerful &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181173/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;suggested concept&lt;/a&gt; that would detect when a pointer is near an¬†element.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Daniel Schwarz &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181174/rss" title="www.alwaystwisted.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Underlining Links with CSS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Stuart shares his own reference guide for styling links beyond the norm. &lt;em&gt;‚ÄúCSS now gives us a whole set of &lt;code&gt;text-decoration&lt;/code&gt; properties that let us get really specific about how our underlines should look and¬†behave‚Äù.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Stuart Robson &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181175/rss" title="www.alwaystwisted.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Typographic Scales in CSS with &lt;code&gt;:heading()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;sibling-index()&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;pow()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Another from Stuart, this time looking at how to build flexible, maintainable typographic scales with just a few lines of¬†code.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Stuart Robson &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 18px;  padding-left: 18px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400 !important; font-size: 1.3em !important; color: #000;"&gt;‚ñ∂¬†¬†&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181168/rss" title="www.youtube.com" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;Interop 2026: Browsers Are Finally Catching Up&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Last week we shared news of &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181169/rss" style=" color: #D94306;"&gt;the Interop efforts for this year&lt;/a&gt;, now Scott and Wes sit down to unpack the browser features looking to aligning across engines, from container style queries and anchor positioning to scroll-driven animations and view¬†transitions.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Syntax &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase; margin-left: 4px; padding-top: 1px; padding-right: 4px;  padding-left: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;             "&gt;podcast&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.0em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/181177/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-size: 1.0em !important; font-weight: 500 !important;"&gt;Honoring Mobile OS Text Size&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî &lt;em&gt;‚ÄúIf your users scale the text size in Android or iDeviceOS, that doesn‚Äôt always affect the size of text on a web¬†page.‚Äù&lt;/em&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="color: #5a5a5a; margin-top: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6em !important;"&gt;Adrian Roselli&lt;/span&gt; 
  &lt;/p&gt;
